      <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-coral/10 text-coral font-mono font-bold text-sm border border-coral/20">07</span>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">Copy Checklist</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Run every piece of copy through this checklist before it goes live. It covers everything from this playbook. If you can check every box, your copy is ready. If not, you know exactly what to fix.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-6">

      <!-- Group 1: Fundamentals -->
      <div class="p-6 bg-navy-light border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-coral uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Fundamentals</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">You know who you're writing for — one specific audience, not "anyone who might want this"</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The #1 outcome (not feature) is stated clearly in the first thing the reader sees</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The copy follows a recognizable framework (PAS, AIDA, BAB, or FAB)</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">There is one and only one primary call to action</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Group 2: Headline -->
      <div class="p-6 bg-navy-light border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-coral uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Headline</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">You wrote at least 10 headline variants before choosing this one</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The headline is outcome-focused, not feature- or tech-focused</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The headline is specific enough that it couldn't describe a competitor's product</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The subheadline adds specifics: who it's for, how it works, or what makes it different</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Group 3: Copy Quality -->
      <div class="p-6 bg-navy-light border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-coral uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Copy Quality</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">Vague words (powerful, robust, seamless, better) have been replaced with specific claims</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">Passive voice has been replaced with active voice throughout</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">Every sentence passes the "so what?" test — the benefit is explicit, not implied</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">Filler words have been cut (very, really, just, quite, in order to)</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">You read it out loud and it sounded like a person talking, not a press release</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Group 4: Language & Voice -->
      <div class="p-6 bg-navy-light border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-coral uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Language & Voice</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">At least one phrase uses the customer's exact language (from support, interviews, or reviews)</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The copy talks about the customer more than it talks about the product</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">If AI was used, the output has been edited with at least one specific detail AI couldn't know</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Group 5: CTA -->
      <div class="p-6 bg-navy-light border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-coral uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Call to Action</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">CTA button text describes what the user gets, not what they do ("Start Building Free" not "Sign Up")</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">There is a friction reducer near the CTA ("No credit card required," "Free forever for solo devs")</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer group">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 accent-coral w-4 h-4 rounded shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed group-hover:text-white transition-colors">The biggest objection a customer might have is addressed somewhere on the page</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-coral/10 to-transparent border-l-4 border-coral pl-6 py-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
        "Copy is never done — it's shipped. Check the essentials, publish, and let real click-through rates and conversions tell you what to improve. A live page that converts at 3% beats a perfect draft sitting in Notion."
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

